    "format-version": "0.1",
    "license": "MIT",
    "name": "Falco-bowtie2",
    "readme": "This workflow is built on top of SABER (System for Automated Bioinformatics Endpoint Reliability), an automated infrastructure for monitoring the status of Galaxy instances. It runs lightweight test jobs\u2014Falco and Bowtie2 alignments on sacCer3 data\u2014on a daily schedule using Jenkins.\n\nThe goal is to ensure prompt failure detection and maintain service reliability across multiple endpoints. The workflow is configurable via encrypted YAML files and produces timestamped, traceable outputs in HTML and Markdown formats. Future improvements include integration with Grafana and support for parallel workflow executions. Monitoring results are available at: https://monitor.usegalaxy.it.\n\nLimitations: This workflow is optimized for test purposes only. It uses synthetic data and minimal runtime configurations, and should not be used for full-scale production analysis.",
    "report": {
        "markdown": "\n# Workflow Execution Report\n\n## Workflow Inputs\n```galaxy\ninvocation_inputs()\n```\n\n## Workflow Outputs\n```galaxy\ninvocation_outputs()\n```\n\n## Workflow\n```galaxy\nworkflow_display()\n```\n"
    },
